The paper focuses on the development of a method for accurately detecting heads in indoor scenes using deep convolutional neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the proposed method involves the use of feature refinement and channel weighting, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of a new dataset for head detection, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
